<promed@promedmail.org>
[MPA seems to join MBM (Meat and bone meals) and frying oil within an
infamous list of food-safety affairs that were strongly related to
recycling - a term which has lost some of its attractiveness following the
BSE and dioxin scandals. Previous experience shows that such an issue
becomes international within days, if not hours. It remains to be seen if
this new one will enjoy an improved crisis management.
ProMED-mail is very grateful to Edu Wijdeveld (Baarn) for bringing the
subject initially to our attention- Mod. AS]
[Medroxyprogesterone acetate is a drug which is used in the treatment of
some cancers. It is a man-made drug which is similar to the female hormone
progesterone. Hormones are substances which are produced naturally in the
body, where they act as chemical messengers and help control the activity
of cells and organs. It is mainly used in the treatment of breast cancer,
but may also be used to treat cancer of the uterus (womb) and occasionally
prostate cancer. It may also be used to treat cancer of the kidney
(hypernephroma) but it is not known how it works in this situation. - Mod.TG]
